<HEADLINE>
American takes the stand in Italy murder trial
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
PERUGIA, Italy 2009-06-12 09:42:44 UTC
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An American student charged with murder and sexual assault has taken the stand in an Italian court in the 2007 killing of her flatmate.
</P>
<P>
Amanda Knox has given brief statements to the Perugia court during the trial, but Friday was the first time she took the witness stand.
</P>
<P>
Knox, an exchange student from Seattle, is on trial with her Italian former boyfriend Raffaele Sollecito.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors contend the two murdered 21-year-old Meredith Kercher during what began as a sex game. They deny wrongdoing.
</P>
<P>
Ivory Coast national Rudy Hermann Guede was found guilty of murder and sexual violence and was sentenced to 30 years in prison in a separate procedure. He, too, denies wrongdoing.
</P>
